第一题

自编写函数实现计算：

t = c(251,801,200,409,415,502,314,1101,980,1124)
hm2 = c(52,101,65,88,90,98,120,150,140,120)

calcor2 = \(x1,x2){
  x1bar = mean(x1,na.rm = T)
  x2bar = mean(x2,na.rm = T)
  cor2 = sum((x1-x1bar)*(x2-x2bar)) / sqrt(sum((x1-x1bar)^2)*sum((x2-x2bar)^2))
  return(cor2)
}

calcor2(t,hm2)
#> [1] 0.8030025

我们测算出来的皮尔逊相关性系数为0.8030025,自由度f为8, 在显著性水平\(\alpha\) = 0.10上查表可得对应的\({r}_{0.10}\) = 0.5494,而 0.8030025 > 0.5494, 所以该地区粮食产量与受灾面积的相关性在0.1的显著性水平下显著

基于r自带的cor和cor.test函数运算

t = c(251,801,200,409,415,502,314,1101,980,1124)
hm2 = c(52,101,65,88,90,98,120,150,140,120)

cor2 = cor(t,hm2,method = "pearson")
cor2
#> [1] 0.8030025
cor.test(t,hm2,method = "pearson")
#> 
#>  Pearson's product-moment correlation
#> 
#> data:  t and hm2
#> t = 3.811, df = 8, p-value = 0.005156
#> alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
#> 95 percent confidence interval:
#>  0.3506740 0.9515389
#> sample estimates:
#>       cor 
#> 0.8030025

第二题

计算如下数据的相关系数并拟合一个一元线性回归

自己写函数求解

h = c(3.34,2.56,0.89,1.57,0.75,1.40,0.99)
d = c(780,510,172,232,138,210,90)
calcor2 = \(x1,x2){
  x1bar = mean(x1,na.rm = T)
  x2bar = mean(x2,na.rm = T)
  cor2 = sum((x1-x1bar)*(x2-x2bar)) / sqrt(sum((x1-x1bar)^2)*sum((x2-x2bar)^2))
  return(cor2)
}

calculm = \(x,y){
  xbar = mean(x,na.rm = T)
  ybar = mean(y,na.rm = T)
  lxx = sum((x - xbar)^2)
  lxy = sum((x-xbar)*(y-ybar))
  bhat = lxy / lxx
  ahat = ybar - bhat * xbar
  yhat = bhat * x + ahat
  Q = sum((y - yhat)^2)
  U = sum((yhat - ybar)^2)
  F_statistic = U / (Q / (length(x) - 2))
  lmv = c(bhat,ahat,F_statistic)
  names(lmv) = c('系数','截距','F统计量')
  return(lmv)
}

calcor2(h,d)
#> [1] 0.9781338
calculm(d,h)
#>         系数         截距      F统计量 
#> 3.777761e-03 4.922591e-01 1.105955e+02

我们测算出来的皮尔逊相关性系数为0.9781338,自由度f为5, 在显著性水平\(\alpha\) = 0.10上查表可得对应的\({r}_{0.10}\) = 0.6694,而 0.8030025 > 0.6694, 所以平均潮差与至150m等深线的最短距离的相关性在0.1的显著性水平下显著

查表可知\({F}_{0.10}\)(1,5) = 4.06,而110.6 > 4.06, 所以该一元线性回归在显著性水平为0.1下显著

基于r的lm和summary函数

h = c(3.34,2.56,0.89,1.57,0.75,1.40,0.99)
d = c(780,510,172,232,138,210,90)

cor(h,d,method = 'pearson')
#> [1] 0.9781338
cor.test(h,d,method = 'pearson')
#> 
#>  Pearson's product-moment correlation
#> 
#> data:  h and d
#> t = 10.516, df = 5, p-value = 0.0001342
#> alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
#> 95 percent confidence interval:
#>  0.8544742 0.9968906
#> sample estimates:
#>       cor 
#> 0.9781338
lm.model = lm(h ~ d, data = data.frame(h,d))
summary(lm.model)
